<n-docbody><doc bill="Y"><content.metadata.block><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.second.line.cite><bop/><bos/>Canada-U.S. Commercial Law Guide § 15:41<eos/><eop/></cmd.second.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block><prop.block><prop.head toc-guid=""><bop/><bos/><headtext>Canada-U.S. Commercial Law Guide</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><content.metadata.block><cmd.dates><cmd.currency.default iso.d="20200901"><bop/><eop/></cmd.currency.default></cmd.dates></content.metadata.block><author.line><bop/><bos/><author>Alison R. Manzer</author><eos/><eop/></author.line><author.line><bop/><bos/><author>Peter Sullivan</author><eos/><eop/></author.line><prop.head toc-guid="Ib5061e30687911ea89fcf2e9bcb61d6d"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Chapter</label.name><label.designator>15.</label.designator><headtext>Securities Law</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><author.line><bop/><bos/><author>Alison Manzer, Jared Puterman, Richard Raymer and Jodie Kaufman Davis[<footnote.reference refid="I2f4015d0fce911ea8c69e91a847d803a">*</footnote.reference>]</author><eos/><eop/></author.line><prop.head toc-guid="Ib51ed650687911ea89fcf2e9bcb61d6d"><bop/><bos/><label.designator>III.</label.designator><headtext>Selected Topics</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head></prop.block><message.block><include.copyright n-include_collection="w_wlnv_msg" n-include_guid="I1DA35ED81DD211B281BAD200220BDFCA">Copyright (c) 2017 Thomson/RIA All rights reserved.</include.copyright></message.block><section><section.front><doc.title toc-guid="If7d3c2369b5f11ea8d59a25188d959d9"><head parent="doc.title"><bop/><bos/><label.name>§ </label.name><label.designator>15:41.</label.designator><headtext>Corporate Governance—Small Issuers</headtext><eos/><eop/></head></doc.title></section.front><section.body><classification.block source="trillium"><para><bop/><tbl ID="abxbrownbeatty-2_1205_49"><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><bos/><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="50*"/><thead><row rowsep="hsingle"><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col1" align="left" valign="top"><para><paratext><bold>Legal Topics</bold></paratext></para><para><paratext>Find other content related to these topics or navigate subheadings within this document.</paratext></para></entry></row><row rowsep="hsingle"><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col1" align="left" valign="top">Legal Topics</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="hsingle"><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col1" align="left" valign="top"><para><paratext><digest.classif><digest.classification ID="" search-string="SEC.I">SEC.I Securities—Constitutional issues</digest.classification></digest.classif></paratext></para></entry></row></tbody></tgroup><eos/></table></tbl><eop/></para></classification.block><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>In General, Smaller Reporting Companies are subject to SOX and Dodd-Frank, and all of the U.S. corporate governance requirements apply to them. <eos/><bos/>However, since the 2008 amendment of the “Small Business Issuer” requirement with the broader category of “Smaller Reporting Companies”, companies with a public float of less than a U.S. $75 million float or less than U.S. $50 million in revenue (if no float exists) have enjoyed a simpler and more streamlined disclosure regime. <eos/><bos/>Many of the current and proposed corporate governance rules in Canada provide some relief for Venture Issuers as well.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></section.body></section><author.footnotes><footnote ID="I2f4015d0fce911ea8c69e91a847d803a"><label.designator>*</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>Updated chapter 2012 by: Alison Manzer, Partner, Cassels Brock &amp; Blackwell LLP, Jared Puterman, Student at Law, Cassels Brock &amp; Blackwell LLP, Richard Raymer, Partner, Dorsey &amp; Whitney LLP and Jodie Kaufman Davis, Associate, Dorsey &amp; Whitney LLP. Original chapter, 2004, by Lori A. Prokopich with Richard B. Raymer of Dorsey &amp; Whitney LLP.</paratext><eos/><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></author.footnotes><content.metadata.block><cmd.royalty><cmd.copyright><bop/><bos/>© 2020 Thomson Reuters Canada Limited<eos/><eop/></cmd.copyright></cmd.royalty><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.first.line.cite><bop/><bos/>MANZERCDA-WL § 15:41<eos/><eop/></cmd.first.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block></doc></n-docbody>
